{
  "stem": "2460.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And two weeks later-- should I continue?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Two weeks later, a truck came with German soldiers with Mengele.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by then, we already knew who is Mengele.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were terrible scared when we heard the name Mengele.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We know that Mengele for us was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was the name frightening, because they told us that he's taking children and he's deciding who goes to work and who doesn't go to work, who gets burned.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we didn't believe that they are burning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even if we were told, we did not believe that people are burned or gassed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We did not believe that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In almost two months in Auschwitz-- seven weeks-- I heard it daily, but we couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] or maybe we just couldn't comprehend that it is a-- that it's possible to burn children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But a day before I left Auschwitz-Birkenau, at night, we were awoken by a terrible yelling and crying and-- it was a terrible-- the sounds were unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The gypsy camp was taken to the crematorias.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, the gypsy camp was a camp in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Our uneven numbers, we were the Hungarian transport, and the gypsies were in the even numbers, just across the street.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Street-- just across the barrack.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Those were all gypsies.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When I saw the gypsies, they were families living together, not like we.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were not wearing the striped clothing that we had.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were wearing civil clothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They looked different.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I remember the gypsies from Slovakia, they were different than we were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But those gypsies, they were good-looking people-- not that the gypsies are not good-looking-- but they did look nothing like gypsies.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I don't even know why they called them gypsies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But those were German gypsies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They were mixed together with Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
